description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a permanent Senior Finance Manager within financial management (central reporting).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in a friendly and welcoming environment, we are looking for someone with very strong Microsoft Excel skills and a good grasp of using and developing financial systems You will be proactive, organised, with excellent attention to detail, and someone who enjoys a challenge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead a small and enthusiastic team and will be keen to quickly build internal and external relationships to improve the quality and timeliness of financial reporting. &lt;span&gt;You will p&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;ropose and implement protocols and processes to improve the monitoring and reporting of financial information and forecasts, utilising appropriate technology to improve efficiency and accuracy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will also be the finance lead for education and training income, working closely with Medical HR and Senior Nursing teams, and be the main point of contact with the Trust&#39;s education funding body. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll also have an opportunity to learn new skills and develop existing knowledge whilst working within a supportive team. If this is something you&#39;re interested in, then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will experience working in one of the largest Teaching hospitals in the country – delivering sustainable high quality clinical care, offering an exceptional experience for our patients; and creating a great place for our staff to work. Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust employs around 18,000 staff across our QMC and City Campus. We provide secondary and tertiary services to a population of around 2.5 million across the East Midlands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris DeKepper Lead Accountant - Central Reporting - chris.dekepper@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
